Cell["The other calculations follow as before.", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.588076782479044*^9, 
  3.588076794629938*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"247b3041-c320-4050-8d4c-\
ae833e5fc5a2"],

Cell["\<\
Cross-relaxation and cross-correlated relaxation terms are readily included \
as off-diagonal elements in the matrix argument of Superoperator. However, a \
relaxation superoperator defined this way does not necessarily correspond to \
a plausible physical mechanism. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.816869972154346*^9, 
  3.816870044521132*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"530a8256-836f-49c1-a51a-\
0196b1ca6f8a"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Closed]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Relaxation Models", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.575611915027603*^9, 3.575611926367559*^9}, {
  3.575613134956509*^9, 3.575613135881061*^9}, {3.5880743881239867`*^9, 
  3.588074393316068*^9}, {3.588076866244617*^9, 
  3.58807688401947*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a4025d18-214e-4800-8aa2-\
3106059676a3"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Realistic relaxation models are simulated in ",
 StyleBox["SpinDynamica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " by specifying the relaxation superoperator which describes a particular \
mechanism within Abragam-Redfield relaxation theory.  Texts such as J. \
Kowalewski and L. M\[ADoubleDot]ler, \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Nuclear Spin \
Relaxation in Liquids: Theory, Experiments and Applications.\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] (CRC Press, Boca Raton, Florida, 2006) may be \
consulted to discover the appropriate form of the relaxation superoperator in \
specific cases. In most cases the relaxation superoperator involves a \
combination of ",
 StyleBox["DoubleCommutationSuperoperator",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " objects. ",
 StyleBox["SpinDynamica",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " is capable of handling very general forms, including arbitrary correlation \
times, motional models, cross-correlation effects, and so on. Only a few \
simple models are given here. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.588076875115369*^9, 
  3.588077087128375*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1c87930e-e216-4629-94c3-\
384f395e1e0f"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Random field relaxation (extreme narrowing)", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.588074747297937*^9, 3.58807475427406*^9}, {
  3.588077054648101*^9, 3.588077057422089*^9}, {3.588077394437627*^9, 
  3.588077400179435*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ef0b4bae-58ff-41c8-a55d-\
88b0be3bf971"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Random field relaxation may be simulated by using a ",
 StyleBox["DoubleCommutationSuperoperator",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " between Cartesian angular momentum operator components. For example, if \
the random field has magnitude \[Omega]rms (in frequency units), and \
correlation time \[Tau]c, then the appropriate relaxation superoperator for \
an isotropic random field, in the extreme narrowing limit, is as follows:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.588077059666685*^9, 3.588077064326393*^9}, {
  3.5880770975637617`*^9, 3.588077196918937*^9}, {3.588077460115395*^9, 
  3.588077460479046*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"99b96347-f4ad-4258-8699-\
3acc6f40686b"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"SetSpinSystem", "[", "1", "]"}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"\[CapitalGamma]ran", "=", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"-", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{"1", "/", "2"}], ")"}]}], 
    SuperscriptBox["\[Omega]rms", "2"], "\[Tau]c", " ", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"DoubleCommutationSuperoperator", "[", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"opI", "[", "\"\<x\>\"", "]"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"opI", "[", "\"\<x\>\"", "]"}]}], "]"}], "+", 
      RowBox[{"DoubleCommutationSuperoperator", "[", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"opI", "[", "\"\<y\>\"", "]"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"opI", "[", "\"\<y\>\"", "]"}]}], "]"}], "+", 
      RowBox[{"DoubleCommutationSuperoperator", "[", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"opI", "[", "\"\<z\>\"", "]"}], ",", 
        RowBox[{"opI", "[", "\"\<z\>\"", "]"}]}], "]"}]}], ")"}]}]}], 
  ";"}]}], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.588077201195537*^9, 3.588077312579234*^9}, 
   3.588077466955693*^9, {3.588077561973204*^9, 3.5880775628240232`*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[44]:=",ExpressionUUID->"1f70d26f-f1b3-40c7-bbd3-089276756218"],

